Hi everyone,



BlinkOn 20 is fast approaching on April 7-8, 2025 PDT, and we’re gratified
to see a great set of content coming together across breakout sessions (sign
up
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScbWXBTq9JUSnx7MDYPdqCaaNaLT4K0lTdTzprsmmnhUD-e6g/viewform"&gt;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScbWXBTq9JUSnx7MDYPdqCaaNaLT4K0lTdTzprsmmnhUD-e6g/viewform&lt;/a&gt;&gt;)
and lightning talks (sign up
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WzayL23cUswDviKf6Op1zfmNo4AgbkPOvVkJst_PpjQ/edit?gid=0#gid=0"&gt;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1WzayL23cUswDviKf6Op1zfmNo4AgbkPOvVkJst_PpjQ/edit?gid=0#gid=0&lt;/a&gt;&gt;)!
If you haven't already done so, don't forget to register now
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdEq_GzXUzMJ98YjNHDzKEkBzlmQKE4osCLDF--CB1pgyRU4g/viewform"&gt;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdEq_GzXUzMJ98YjNHDzKEkBzlmQKE4osCLDF--CB1pgyRU4g/viewform&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
.



Schedule

You can view the draft schedule here
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QlHK8kgnAA_d48MTjESpxl8w3hkXFhSzv3oBEkFYyco/edit?gid=1283479804#gid=1283479804"&gt;https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QlHK8kgnAA_d48MTjESpxl8w3hkXFhSzv3oBEkFYyco/edit?gid=1283479804#gid=1283479804&lt;/a&gt;&gt;.
Each room (row 1) will have a unique Google Meet ID.

It’s rapidly filling up, and we’re hearing some desire for additional types
of lightweight presentations and dialog with other attendees. To support
this, we’re introducing a new Unconference Track as an experiment for
BlinkOn 20.

Unconference Track (both days after lunch)

BlinkOn 20 will have space for lightly-structured presentations and dialog
after the lunch breaks on both days. Sign ups will happen via this Google
Form
&lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScjT868OcW1n-mP3TMgJ811puh7DXFkBZ4j4IWkRBQ3k6Cmog/viewform"&gt;https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScjT868OcW1n-mP3TMgJ811puh7DXFkBZ4j4IWkRBQ3k6Cmog/viewform&lt;/a&gt;&gt;
starting on day one of BlinkOn 20.

These are up to thirty minute sessions focused on lightweight presentation
and/or conversation with attendees around a topic - it could be a new
proposal or exploration, group brainstorming around an emerging problem, or
a shared interest.

Due to the nature of the topics, A/V support and recordings will not be
provided - Unconference Track is optimized for dynamic in-person
discussions. We hope this will support making new connections and exploring
new ideas this year, and look forward to your feedback!

If you have any questions, please email us at blin...@chromium.org.

Thanks,

Lutz on behalf of the BlinkOn Planning Committee


